# ParaguAI Brand Visual Rule

## Purpose

Any social image, carousel, ad creative, or AI-generated graphic for **ParaguAI** must use the **official** name and logo from [paragu-ai.com](https://paragu-ai.com/), not approximations.

## Mandatory reference

Before generating or approving ParaguAI visuals, read:

`AI-Whisperers-Marketing-Hub/Campaigns/ParaguAI/brand/PARAGUAI-BRAND-GUIDE.md`

Use local logo file:

`AI-Whisperers-Marketing-Hub/Campaigns/ParaguAI/brand/paraguai-logo.png`

When using image generation tools, pass `paraguai-logo.png` as a **reference image** whenever the tool supports it.

## Name (non-negotiable)

- **ParaguAI** — single word, capital P, capital AI in wordmark styling.
- Product line name on corporate pieces: **ParaguAI Builder**.
- URL: **paragu-ai.com** (lowercase, hyphen).

Never: Paragu AI, ParaguayAI, PARAGU AI, or generic "AI company" logos.

## Logo (non-negotiable)

- **Icon:** square, diagonal split, purple-pink gradient (top-left), dark navy (bottom-right), white **AI**.
- **Wordmark:** navy pill, white **Paragu**, lavender **AI**.
- Do not substitute a different icon, recolor the gradient, or use stock "AI brain" clipart.

## Workflow for new images

1. **Document first:** create or update `verticals/{slug}/image-prompt-es.md` (or `brand/image-prompts/PROMPT-*.md` for global assets). Complete the pre-generation checklist in that file.
2. Load `paraguai-logo.png` as reference.
3. Apply rubro-specific **content** colors only outside the logo lockup.
4. Place official logo + `paragu-ai.com` on every published square/landscape creative.
5. If generated output drifts from the reference, **composite the official PNG** in Figma/Canva instead of accepting the drift.

## Copy alignment

Social prompts and posts under `Campaigns/ParaguAI/` must link to the correct demo URL per vertical (e.g. `gymfit-py`, `salon-maria`) when promoting a template.

## Outputs

- **Per vertical:** `Campaigns/ParaguAI/verticals/{slug}/social-1080.png` after `image-prompt-es.md` is approved.
- **Global campaign pieces:** `Campaigns/ParaguAI/assets/` only with a matching approved prompt in `brand/image-prompts/` (e.g. `PROMPT-{name}-es.md`).
- Document which prompt file was used in the post markdown or vertical README.

## Anti-patterns

- Inventing a new "ParaguAI" logotype per post.
- English-only brand name on Spanish PY audience posts (name stays **ParaguAI**; copy can be Spanish).
- Publishing without the logo because "the layout was cleaner".
